<p>Yes, they did have a very good show, and even early on in the season, people knew that they would sweep at the finals. They had to take down the reigning two-time champs, The Blue Devils, to win it, and they won by a good margin, winning by 1.275pts. In the marching world, it is very common for the pts margin to be within a few tenths of a point, so the fact that they were able to defeat the reigning champ by over a point says a lot about that year’s show. With it being a very dominant show of that year, is it the highest-scoring show ever? Again, no, it wasn’t. That title goes to the 2014 Blue Devils. You can see here in the second chart that they scored a whopping 99.8pts.</p>
