<p>They were only .2 away from a perfect show, which a perfect show has never happened. I would also like to point out that the margin from the first place show to the second place show is a pretty big margin as well. Why am I showing you this? Well, to show that I am wrong, partially, but I wasn’t that far off from my original idea. Even though this was not the most dominant show ever, it is in the top 5 highest scoring shows, but top scores are not the only thing that shows dominance in DCI. The point margin from first to second place is a very good way, and probably the best way to show how dominant a show was. Looking at this third chart, you can see just how large the margin is from first to second place. While the exact points are not shown, you can see just how large some of the gaps were from gold to silver. While the margin from the 2018 show is very large again, the largest gap from first to second place goes to the 2014 Blue Devils. They managed to win by over 2.5pts, which is insane.</p>
